description.narrative: By 2016, key policies and strategies necessary for responding to emergency and scale up of high impact integrated interventions are coordinated, strengthened and implemented in functioning Health District/Prefecture (2012-2014) Effective and efficient programme management, supply, logistics and operational support to programme delivery), which contributes to Child Health, Health Systems Strengthening. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2016, at least 60% of girls and boys under-five and pregnant / lactating women use high impact gender-responsive integrated services (curative, preventive and promotional) in the country for an accelerated reduction of infant and under five mortality and maternal mortality.
